##After mainland students return to Hong Kong

WECHAT liveulife

Features, occasional travel notes, film reviews, essays on life

The previous article mentioned that HKU required mainland students to return to Hong Kong in self-imposed isolation for 14 days before they could return to their dormitories and campuses, and that the university had not explicitly addressed the issues of isolation accommodation and meals. This article is to record the follow-up measures taken by schools and the Hong Kong government. I do have a lot of dissatisfaction with the school, but I also realize that when it comes to personal rights, compared with some mainland administrators, Hong Kong universities and the government are more humane. They can hear your opinions, you can also go on to help improve your situation -- but you have to speak up and say what I want; the silent person gets nothing.

The Hong Kong government attaches great importance to the condition mainly in the information disclosure and the mandatory isolation measures. Through the Hong Kong government's website, you can see the latest disease data and disease map at any time. The Red Dot on the map refers to the recent residence of the confirmed case, and can be specific to a certain street, a certain building. (for me, the distance is worrying.)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As for the mandatory quarantine, the Hong Kong government has imposed mandatory quarantine on all persons returning to Hong Kong from the mainland since February 8, and has banned the entry of persons holding tourist visas (for only seven days) , that means only those holding Hong Kong resident identity cards (University Students) / permanent identity cards can come back. One of the most important steps to take after filling out the form is to add WHATSAPP, because the quarantined person is obliged to undergo random surprise checks for the next 14 days, and report your location via WHATSAPP'S GPS to the central government, making sure you stay in an isolated roomhotel every day. The address depends on the individual. If you have a place in Hong Kong, such as a rented house, you may be asked to return to the rented house in isolation. The Three Meals a Day will bring you free food and supplies (thermometer, etc.)  It could also be people staying at government-arranged resorts without accommodation) ; the last is quarantined by hotels in Hong Kong arranged by their schools / companies.

Of the three options, the safest is surely hotel segregation, as renting is still a possibility to congregate, and resorts do not guarantee single room isolation. In this regard, HKU has done a good job, for students returning from the mainland before February 20 to arrange for three-star to four-star hotel single room isolation, in ctrip look at these hotels a night of about 500 to 700. The Three Meals a Day is staffed by professionals, and there are people downstairs who check in on students to make sure everyone stays inside and stays out of the way. However, when these arrangements are made for individuals, it is still inevitable that there will be a lot of chaos. For example, during the quarantine period, the mobile phone is out of service but can not go to the counter, and the down jacket worn from the mainland has been left without a place to wash for 14 days, the caterers were late, worried that the air conditioning in the hotel would blow the droplets into their rooms, and so on.

When the 14-day isolation period is over, the mainlanders can return to their dormitories on campus. However, there are some requirements inside the dormitory, such as all students entering the dormitory have to undergo a temperature check, no one outside the dormitory is allowed to enter, and so on. These management methods and the mainland's more similar to the plot, not to say much.

It is worth mentioning that the daily cleaning work of the dormitory is very good. In my dormitory, for example, there will be a basic cleaning and disinfection every hour. There will be a cleaning and disinfection of the toilet in the morning and at noon respectively, every day, the food waste will be handled by a special cleaning lady (we usually call her sister Kim) on this floor. In addition, each floor of the student dormitory next to the elevator will have an alcohol gel hand sanitizer, alcohol with the head of the pump to wash hands. On the laundry room, public space, and lobby floors, install another device that automatically squirts out alcohol-based hand sanitizer without pressing. And each floor of the toilet, there is a device for the toilet cover disinfection, before going to the toilet, you can use it to wipe the surrounding.

The above-mentioned student experience is actually very good, because there are actually many students trapped in Hubei. And the school has said it will only be able to provide free accommodation for students who return before February 22, and those who return to Hong Kong for quarantine will have to pay for it at their own expense, for those who have managed to return to Hong Kong from Hubei, I am afraid it is another problem.

That's all for now. I'M GONNA go watch my online class. I hope everyone's okay.
